modules.description: This module provides low-level arithmetic, bitwise, and comparison operations for 64-bit integers (`int64` and a dedicated `Beint.t` type), emphasizing precise overflow behavior and bit-level manipulation. It supports conversions to/from other numeric types (`int`, `float`, `int32`), string parsing/formatting, and both signed and unsigned comparisons, catering to use cases requiring exact numeric representation or interoperability with system-level data. Hashing utilities and constants are included to facilitate integration with data structures like hash tables, alongside functions for arithmetic shifts and logical operations.
